resourcePressureTask : PlannedTask
resourcePressureTask =
  PlannedTask {
    taskId = agentPlannerTaskIdDiskResourcePressure,
    role = "resource-guard-worker",
    detail = "Recover enough disk headroom for the manager to continue safely.",
    dependencies = emptyTexts,
    taskPrompt = "Use the planner resource health section to recover disk headroom without broad builds, broad verification, swarm restarts, or broad process kills. Start with the ordinary Clasp GeneratedStateCleanupPlan helper in plan mode, preserve manager health lines such as generated-state-cleanup-action=, generated-state-cleanup-safe-to-clean=, generated-state-cleanup-total-reclaimable-mb=, generated-state-cleanup-projected-available-mb=, generated-state-cleanup-can-satisfy-reserve=, generated-state-cleanup-can-satisfy-guard=, generated-state-cleanup-guard-shortfall-after-cleanup-mb=, and generated-state-cleanup-apply-requires=, inspect its cleanup projection fields such as repoReclaimableMb, projectedAvailableMb, cleanupCanSatisfyReserve, cleanupCanSatisfyGuard, and guardShortfallAfterCleanupMb, optionally steer it with CLASP_GENERATED_STATE_CLEANUP_TARGETS_JSON, CLASP_GENERATED_STATE_CLEANUP_TARGETS_PATH, or workspace .clasp-generated-state/cleanup-targets.json, rerun it with CLASP_GENERATED_STATE_APPLY_JSON=true only when safeToClean is true and the projection shows cleanup can help, use scripts/clasp-clean-generated-state.sh --health --json only as an operator fallback for external cache scans, and otherwise report the exact external disk shortfall.",
    coordinationFocus = ["resource-pressure", "generated-state-cleanup", "workspaceRemovePath", "bounded-verification"]
  }

memoryResourcePressureTask : PlannedTask
memoryResourcePressureTask =
  PlannedTask {
    taskId = agentPlannerTaskIdMemoryResourcePressure,
    role = "resource-memory-guard-worker",
    detail = "Reduce launch pressure from memory and unmanaged external-agent RSS before the manager launches more children.",
    dependencies = emptyTexts,
    taskPrompt = "Use the planner resource health memory-admission and memory-concurrency-admission lines, the older memory summary fields, or managed-job memory-exceeded facts to recover memory admission headroom without broad builds, broad verification, swarm restarts, or broad process kills. Preserve and report memory-admission status=, reason=, action=, requiredMb=, headroomMb=, projectedActiveChildren=, externalAgentReservedMb=, plus memory-concurrency-admission configuredMaxChildren=, capacityLimit=, admittedChildCapacity=, effectiveMaxChildren=, and action= when present. Do not use generated-state cleanup as the primary fix for memory or external-agent RSS pressure. First reduce ordinary Clasp manager demand by lowering CLASP_MANAGER_MAX_CONCURRENT_CHILDREN_JSON to the admittedChildCapacity or effectiveMaxChildren from memory-concurrency-admission, lowering CLASP_MANAGER_MAX_TASKS_JSON or the prompt Plan 1-N budget, or editing CLASP_LOCAL_PLANNER_TASK_CATALOG_JSON, CLASP_LOCAL_PLANNER_TASK_CATALOG_PATH, or workspace .clasp-local-planner/task-catalog.json so the next wave emits fewer serialized tasks. Then lower role-specific caps or reserves when safe: CLASP_LOOP_AGENT_MEMORY_MB_JSON, CLASP_LOOP_BUILDER_MEMORY_MB_JSON, CLASP_LOOP_VERIFIER_MEMORY_MB_JSON, CLASP_MANAGER_PLANNER_MEMORY_MB_JSON, CLASP_MANAGER_CHILD_MEMORY_RESERVE_MB_JSON, and CLASP_MANAGER_MIN_AVAILABLE_MEMORY_MB_JSON. If a forced current-shell verifier path is the blocker, lower CLASP_VERIFY_DIRECT_MEMORY_LIMIT_MB or CLASP_VERIFY_AFFECTED_DIRECT_MEMORY_LIMIT_MB before rerunning focused verification, and do not disable CLASP_VERIFY_DIRECT_MEMORY_LIMIT or CLASP_VERIFY_AFFECTED_DIRECT_MEMORY_LIMIT except inside tiny harness fixtures. If unmanaged agent RSS is the blocker, inspect CLASP_MANAGER_EXTERNAL_AGENT_PROCESS_NAMES_JSON and CLASP_MANAGER_EXTERNAL_AGENT_RESERVE_MB_JSON, wait for live external agents to finish, or stop only exact managed jobs identified by metadata when the manager owns them. Use CLASP_MANAGER_RESOURCE_RECOVERY_EXTRA_WAVES_JSON only to allow a bounded recovery replan after reducing demand. Report the exact available_memory_mb, required_available_memory_mb, configuredMaxChildren=, capacityLimit=, admittedChildCapacity=, effectiveMaxChildren=, externalAgentRssMb=, externalAgentReservedMb=, unmanagedRssMb=, directVerifyLimitMb=, or affectedDirectVerifyLimitMb= shortfall when no safe local action exists.",
    coordinationFocus = ["resource-pressure", "memory-pressure", "external-agent-rss", "managed-job-admission", "direct-verifier-memory-cap", "bounded-verification"]
  }

affectedVerificationLaunchTask : PlannedTask
affectedVerificationLaunchTask =
  PlannedTask {
    taskId = agentPlannerTaskIdAffectedVerifierLaunch,
    role = "verifier-launch-worker",
    detail = "Close affected-verifier launch-policy gaps before spawning follow-up verifier work.",
    dependencies = emptyTexts,
    taskPrompt = "Use the affectedVerificationLaunchPolicy, affected-launch-* evidence, focused_verification_plan capability evidence, AgentFocusedVerificationLaunchPolicy evidence, or a Focused verification launch policy JSON block from the context pack to decide the next verifier step before launching more work. Preserve and report affected-launch-mode=, affected-launch-ready=, affected-launch-can-run-direct=, affected-launch-can-run-without-compiler-state=, affected-launch-requires-managed=, affected-launch-recommendation=, focused-verification-plan-command=, focused-verification-plan-safe-direct=, focused-verification-plan-managed-required=, focused-verification-launch-mode=, focused-verification-launch-ready=, focused-verification-launch-recommendation=, focused-verification-launch-policy-mode:, focused-verification-launch-policy-recommendation:, Focused verification launch policy JSON, blockingGaps, and requiredClosure. If mode is direct-compiler-state-access, do not treat the plan as OOM-free: rerun verify-affected --plan-only first, isolate or reset temporary compiler/cache probes where possible, and run only the named safe-direct commands after confirming no broader compiler build is selected. If mode is focused-managed or heavy-managed, or focused_verification_plan launch policy reports managed-required, safe-direct=false, managed-required=true, or JSON mode=managed-required, run the affected or focused verifier only through scripts/verify-affected.sh or scripts/run-managed-job.sh with explicit memory, disk, and low-parallelism admission; never run full verify-all, promotion, broad native-image rebuilds, or unmanaged compiler work from this task. If the affected policy is invalid-plan or the focused_verification_plan launch policy reports invalid-plan or JSON mode=invalid-plan, repair the changed-file list, plan JSON, or Focused verification plan section before any verifier process starts.",
    coordinationFocus = ["affected-verification", "launch-policy", "compiler-cache-state", "managed-verifier-admission", "bounded-verification"]
  }

